	<a name="107273429283025561">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h1>Information Systems</h1><h2>Collaborative Computing</h2><h3>Document Processing</h3>This is a cross-over topic.&nbsp; Here are some items gleaned while scanning through some of my blue-oxen backlog.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.interactivetools.com/products/htmlarea/">interactivetools.com : htmlArea</a>.&nbsp; The other part of Jack Park's tip.&nbsp; I have seen this before.&nbsp; I think it is interesting.&nbsp; I would want to adapt it for any web-based editor, such as for a Blog/Wiki.&nbsp; I haven't looked beyond the surface.&nbsp; I should come back here and get more information, especially about the license.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#107273429283025561">Monday, December 29, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="107273394676458005">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://dynarch.com/mishoo/calendar.epl">[Mishoo] The DHTML Calendar</a>.&nbsp; Jack Park is always finding links to cool things.  Here is a DHTML Calendar object with an LGPL license.&nbsp; The whole thing is on SourceForge.&nbsp; And the calendar widget is very cool.&nbsp; It reminds me of the fun I once had manipulating dates, and I should look at this, and that, to see what I can make of it.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#107273394676458005">Monday, December 29, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
